<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="25Nov1922"><font color="red">25 November 1922</font>, <cite>Letters III</cite> (JJ to Harriet Weaver): My eyes have not been and are not well &hellip; Everything else sent me to Nice was forwarded. Strange to say the writer whom I mentioned in my letter asking for them &mdash; Mr Marcel Proust &mdash; died this day week. His name has often been coupled with mine &hellip; I am sure you are anxious to be away in Cheshire. King Beaver will never find you there. </div>
